caption: I have three since they were out of most of the food options, also THE CHARGE $2 for extra chili / chili oil and any extra condiments you may need.  Plussssssss idk if this is a DC thing but they made our party sign a waiver to dine inside and our contact info/ do temperature checks..... idk super weird and rubbed me the wrong way....! (I’m from Arizona and this took me off guard).  The food was good the pad Thai was unique to say the least...... ordered it “Thai Medium” ....Sorry to spill the “tea” but the Pad Thai here is not the best Pad Thai in dc or the USA so let me be the one to burst the bubble.  The Cosmopolitan was good and tasty as well as my Moscow mule.  Cute location and friendly staff, if you like  Thai food done sweet this is for you. ✅
This place is great. Enough said.
I’ve done a lot of takeout during COVID and this is one of the best! Beautiful Thai dishes with tons of flavor. Highly recommend!

Went to visit after about a year, I enjoyed my food and service was okay. They used a machine to ring me out on my bill. With tax $68. I’ll admit I’m not a big spender but a server has to do something to earn more. This server took it upon himself to adjust the tip I allowed.  When I called to address the matter the manager, Johnny gave me a song about them risking their lives and for my $3 I could keep it because they don’t need it.  A few minutes later he called back to tell me that something was omitted on my check and that should make it about right. I agreed to accept the decision but I am doing this review because management was extremely rude and how the tip issue was handled was illegal. If the server was legitimate I would not have had to go into the place and ask for a receipt. BEWARE COVID is creating criminals
Possibly the best Pad Thai in DC - and there is a lot of competition! Really appreciate that their noodles are gluten-free, too.
The food was delicious and the heaters on the outdoor patio kept us toasty while we ate. The green curry noodles dish is rich and flavorful.
Best Thai food I've ever had.
Very nice Thai food and different from the usual fare. I've been here a number of times and always is a pleasant surprise.
(Translated by Google) Very good quality Thailand's food  (Original) Muy bien es de calidad comida Thailand's
Best pad thai I had!

I haven't been to the physical location yet due to The Rona™️, but I ordered in from here and my god. SO good. The rice was superb: pleasantly spicy, savory, and slightly sweet. They really do it all. The soup that came with the rice stir fry & minced pork was incredible even on it's own! I was expecting plain broth with some green onion thrown in, but there was so much more to it--even a little hint of baking spice.  Absolutely delicious, even delivered thirty minutes after it was made.

This is the best take out  (or dine it post COVID) Thai place in DC. I have tried a lot of Pad Thai (including in Thailand) and BKK has some of the absolute best. Their spicy basil rice is amazing as well as their bangkok noodles. Highly recommend
Amazing food! Love the patio seating
Awesome spot to buy something when in a rush. The customer service is rapid, pricing is convenient, good character. I highly recommend this place

I visited the place twice and both times the noodles were not that great and did not even finish the food. Price is not cheap, I paid over $20 for small a bowl and regretted it. Maybe I will try something else next time.
Absolutely delicious. Ordered the spicy basil rice and wings and WOW, did they deliver (no pun intended). I will absolutely be ordering from here again!
Grabbed a meal for family dinner last night, and we all absolutely loved it. Fantastic flavors, spice, and experience. Will be ordering from here again soon!
Love this place.
Love this place. The boat noodle bowl is by far my favorite. The bowls are comparable size wise to ramen, so be hungry. The soy sauce, garlic and cinnamon broth is utterly delicious.

username: m i c h a e l

caption: Excellent flavorful food, lovely staff. During late lunchtime did have a person come in from street and solicit 2 single woman diners, then cause disruption in bathroom after being aggressive with only visible staff, again a woman. Have since returned with no issues but staff should watch out for each other more.
Great place for a date   CA

This is a hidden gem. Quality street Thai food in the heart of Shaw DC. My friend and I stopped by and ordered the spring rolls, chicken fried rice and beef pad Thai. The rolls were stuffed with meat and fried to perfection. The rice had some heat and awesome textured. The pad Thai was plentiful and very generous in quantity. The drinks and happy hour specials here are great as well. Our service was awesome and the food came out quickly. Flavors on point and not overly expensive. If you want authentic Thai food this is your spot
Really pathetic service - staff is unresponsive and impolite.

The Beau Thai cocktail (which is basically Thai iced tea with chili vodka) was amazing!! The server recommended the Suki Noodle Bowl which was also delicious with tofu.  The service was good, striking a perfect balance between tending to our table and leaving us alone. I would highly recommend this place, it was great!
Authentic Thai food!
This spot is worth visiting. They serve big portions for reasonable prices. Regularly well kept and with good mood. Will come back again.
Very interesting food here. Awesomely delicious
Nice ab abeyance

I asked for my food to be cooked without spicyness. When I got the food home it had hot chillies in it. The place is nearby so I brought it back apologized told them I asked for no spicy. They said they would remake. I walked back home they had taken out all the chillies on top but left the chillies on the bottom. They claimed that mild, no spicy means still include some chillies. Today I decided to give them another chance. Went to place an order and was told none of the food comes mild. And recipes which were made mild in the past could not be made mild. Won't be coming back here ever again
Pretty good take on modern Thai
Great tasty flavorfull food. The buns appetizers are a must! Wine was also great. Loved it. Go for it!
Great selection of noodles! Huge portions and delicious food. Very cute interior as well - great neighborhood spot overall.
Take out. Food was good. I like it portion were appropriate. Next time I want the whole restaurant experience.

Delicious food and a beautiful and welcoming atmosphere! The wine selection was also very nice. I ordered the coconut curry noodle bowl with tofu and it was delicious. Great service as well. Will definitely be coming back!
Like the spicy food then this is your place. Try the Thai tea.

The food here are all very good. The noodle dishes are all excellent. Dining in can be a little depressing, emptied most time which leads to almost no service. Sad to always having to wave someone down for anything, especially when its not busy at all. They do decent amount of take out food, maybe I'll just stick to that. Love the food but not wow on the experience.
This is now my first and last stop in DC for Thai food. Will visit again.  Also, Thai spicy is that spicy, and that delicious. 😂
The team is friendly, the food was quickly prepared for takeout, but it was mediocre. Nothing I'd complain about, but I probably will not return.
I hadn’t eaten really well cooked drunken noodles in in a long time, then I stumbled upon this beautiful cookshop. They cook for real...with fresh ingredients. I absolutely loved it.😍
Delicious food and good ambience. Really liked the suki noodle dish.
Great everything

Ok thai, pad thai was tasty but unexciting overall, not spicy (even though we asked) but good sized portion. Nice patio outside to eat on. Service a little scattered (seemed like the waiters weren't communicating to coordinate themselves much but maybe it was just one of those nights.
Interesting place. Don't ask to use the restroom unless you are a patron just a heads up. Nice atmosphere though.
Wonderful! Delicious apps, helpful server.. all around delicious!
Green Curry and cucumber salad!

I and my two teens we're hungry for Thai after a long sightseeing day in DC. This is not your grandparents' Thai restaurant. The decor is urban contemporary, clean lines and neutral colors. Seating styles range from two-tops to bar-style seating to a large communal table. Approximately 20 people were there when we arrived. The service was outstanding, attentive but not too much, swift and helpful. I'd say that not one of them were over 35. Entrees we're very reasonable, ranging from $10-15. We had Spring Rolls, Chicken Pad Thai, Drunken Noodles with pork, and Coconut Curry Noodle Bowl with tofu. Everything was delicious and beautifully presented. We could not have been happier. Well worth your time and money.
Delicious! Not sure why I've waited this long to come here!

Pleasant place with good food I went to this small restaurant with a friend. We sat outside We ordered Spring Rolls, Beef Satay, Chicken Pad Thai & Pork Drunken Noodles. Everything was very tasty and appetizing and the service was ok. One warning though, their satay is spicy even though the menu doesn't list it as such!
Great noodles. The Brussels sprouts are amazing.

Visited BKK recently for a lunch meeting. I loved that we were immediately greeted when we walked in and directed to a seat. We ordered the steamed buns as an appetizer and sadly they were not heated through, it was still frozen in the center. We had to send it back to be reheated. The waiter apologized took it back and brought it back fully heated through. I ordered the Bangkok Spicy Noodles and it was delicious. It’s was the best meal for a cold day. I enjoyed my dining experience and I would go back for sure.
Always good always cosy.
Terrible experience. The drunken noodles were undercooked and rolled up. Everything was dry and tasteless. Worst Thai food I've ever had.
Went there two times to pick up food and had both bad experiences with waitresses they’re racist , was waiting my food they told me to get off the chair for Customers. Will never go there again 😡
This place is great!! The pad Thai is delicious and it’s a great spot for a weeknight bite. They have some picnic tables that are nice to hang out on in the summer time
Great little Thai place. Speedy and very courteous service.
Pad Thai, and I happy as a pig rolling around in do-do.

Delicious pad thai and great happy hour specials. $3 beerlaos will keep me coming back. The beef pad thai is some of the best pad thai I've had so that will keep me coming back even moreso. Nice atmosphere and fast service.
Some of the best fried rice and stir fry noodle my boyfriend and I have had! Definitely recommend the sukiyaki stirfry, it was super yummy with the right amount of spiciness to it
Great neighborhood spot. Good for takeout too.
One of my favorite places in DC--the coconut noodle soup is the best, and the buns delicious. Great low-key date spot, or casual dinner with friends.

I've only ordered delivery from here, but I LOVE the pad thai. The portion size is perfect (usually you'll get way too much food, but I eat the whole thing when I order from here). It's SO good. Definitely recommend!
Amazing service and food.
Have Not tried much but love the feel
Very tasty Thai. The spicy noodle dish was very spicy in a good way, with clean flavors.
food is bland
The layout is a little weird, but the food was fantastic!
Noodles

Nice location, especially during good weather. Food is what you would expect: I don't think DC has really terrific Thai food, but this is enjoyable and what you think of when you order Phad Thai or other noodles/dishes. The staff is nice, especially if you interact wit them and don't use GrubHub or another delivery service (really: if you're in the neighborhood, just drop by and see them to pick up food. Everyone really appreciates the in-person interaction).

I’ve never actually eaten in here, but this is my go-to carry out spot in the area. It’s a more limited menu, pretty much all noodles and some apps, but I’m not complaining. All of their food has just as much flavor as you’d get eating from street vendors in Bangkok, and they have a lot behind pad Thai and green curry. (Although those are my two go-tos here ...) Friendly service when you go to pick it up, so maybe someday I’ll give the dine-in a shot :)
Convient nice outside for summer. Food was acceptable, but there are better Thai soups around for the price.
Best Thai food I've has since being in Thailand. Ambiance is bomb, beer is cold, and portions are plentiful. This place makes me want to be a better person.
Pad Thai was delicious
Decent food, very spicy and a great patio and happy hour! The brussel sprouts were great.
Nasty food .
Very nice range of tasty dishes. Casual and informal.
Great service and excellent food selections. Portions were good but not too expensive.

BKK is the sister restaurant for Beau Thai featuring noodle bowls and Thai street food. Everything I've had here is amazing. I love the green curry noodle bowl and the steam buns (the chicken curry one is super spicy! I love it). I like to get to cucumber salad to balance out the spicy.  They also deliver in the neighborhood!
Delicious food at each and every visit--and they deliver through uberEats. Try the iced coffee, it's amazing.

Ordered take-out a few days ago. Incredibly tasty food--although most of it was too spicy for me (I have a low spice threshold). Will definitely be returning to order some less spicy items in the future!
The hot and spicy noodle bowl is the best bowl of noodle soup in the whole city!

Great food and friendly staff. All their appetizers are great, but my favourite is the brussel sprouts. They do staples very well (Pad Thai and Drunken Noodles), and have some yummy spicy special dishes.

After 3 days at a conference and a night out drinking I was feeling tired and cold. This place was the remedy! Boat noodles was delicious, dark, intense, warming and I had energy to keep going when I left!
I had the green curry with chicken and it was delicious.  It was pretty spicy/hot, but I like it like that.  Good stuff!
Unique and interesting Thai dishes in a cozy neighborhood spot.  Stands out as one of DC's best Thai restaurants.
great！
Almost as good as beau thai, same owners.
A bit cheaper than Beau Thai and lots of investing things to try on the appetizer menu. The Son-in-law eggs were my favorite.
On the pricey side for Thai food, but I got the fiery basil rice to carry out, and it was delicious. Proper Chinese broccoli and everything. Hip interior makes this a good date spot, too.
Great riffs on Thai

Gluten-free noodle dishes? Yes please! My wife can't have gluten and this place satisfies her craving for a solid Thai noodle dish. I liked the stir-fried noodles as well and would happily return here again. Fair wine selection to pair with our meal and decent prices for the city. A solid location in the Bloomingdale / Ledroit Park area.
The menu isn't very extensive, but everything I tried was excellent.
Good and spicy food.  I liked it.
Yummy pad Thai, spicy drunken noodles, and delicious coconut curry. Get the steamed buns appetizer for sure. Originally reviewed 4 out of 5, after revisiting, given 5 out of 5.

Food- good, and several tasty noodle dishes. There isn't a bar, but you can get a beer or sake or other drink to cool off. It is predominately a Thai place but don't expect the laundry list of typical Thai dishes. It's a neighborhood place, a place you can count on. When there was snow and almost everything was closed or closing BKK was open.
Thai wings are the best!!! Only bad part is that you only get 4.  If you're close its worth a visit.
So glad to have interesting, innovative Thai street food in the east Shaw/Bloomingdale area. The coconut noodle soup and the son-in-law eggs are beyond delicious -- I could eat them every week.
The Food is delicious!
Some of the best Thai in the city.  Be sure to get the Thai version of churros
Friendly staff. The Thai tea is on point. The coconut broth bowl is simply delightful. Just the right level of spice and flavor. Not on the cheap side.

BKK is superb. Spicy chicken wings are not for the faint of palate and are terrific. Buns are soft and varied: chicken is spicy, black been is sweet, veggie is savory and different. Noodle bowls are delicious; both the udon with vegetable tempura and spicy pork bowls hit the spot. Service is friendly and accommodating.

At lunch today I popped by for the first time and ordered their key dishes. Their pork dish was served to me partially cold and everything I ate felt like it was behind reheated. Now this is a weekday lunch and no one else was eating but it's lame to serve reheated food!

My husband, very large dog, and I just moved from U Street to Shaw, and we are now half a block from BKK. We discovered the restaurant while we were house hunting, stopping in for iced coffees one hot Saturday. The coffee was amazing, and when we realized it was actually a Thai restaurant we were excited to come back and check it out for dinner. Which we did, with our dog, that very night. They have two beautiful patios, so we sat outside with our four-legged dude. The servers, especially Chai, were so nice and brought water and dog biscuits out. We got there early enough to take advantage of some of the happy hour food and wine deals, and we loved the tofu appetizer that was on special. We also had spicy pork buns, which are now one of our favorite dishes in DC. We each had noodle soup dishes, I got the hot and spicy and was happy to find it was indeed spicy - the hotter the better for me!  Since that first dinner, we bought a house in the hood and we have been back several times. In fact we hit up BKK again (again sitting outside with our dog) on our first night in the new place. We've gotten to know management and we're so happy to live right next to such a friendly and delicious place.
